  "market_context": "Gold trading on the 1-hour timeframe around Dec 11–12, 2024, price rallied into the previous day high near 2840 after an uptrend from the 2780 area. Question was whether price would break out through the PDH or form a reversal.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept the previous day high, then formed a change in state of delivery via opposing candles, signaling a reversal off the key level and the start of a new expansion phase lower with a shallow wick supporting downside continuation.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the previous day high as the key liquidity level and ask whether price breaks out or reverses there.",
    "Step 2: Observe price sweeping the previous day high.",
    "Step 3: Mark out the opposing candles, confirming a change in state of delivery at the high.",
    "Step 4: Anticipate a reversal that initiates a new expansion phase lower (consolidation → manipulation → reversal).",
    "Step 5: Confirm expansion lower with a shallow wick supporting continued downside delivery.",
    "Step 6: Track the next leg — note large range into smaller range (retracement), then a new opposing candle forming a protected swing.",
    "Step 7: Retest of the protected swing followed by continued trend lower, completing the expansion–retracement–expansion sequence."
  ],
